theorem Topology.interiorClosure_subset_of_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hAB : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure B) :
    interior (closure A) ⊆ closure B := by
  intro x hx
  -- From `hx`, we have `x ∈ closure A`.
  have hx_closureA : x ∈ closure A :=
    (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A) hx
  -- Since `A ⊆ closure B`, taking closures yields `closure A ⊆ closure B`.
  have h_closure_subset : closure A ⊆ closure B :=
    closure_mono hAB
  -- Combine the two facts to obtain the desired membership.
  exact h_closure_subset hx_closureA
